  "body": "Opening this issue to brainstorm testing strategies for fork choice for a local containerized environment:\r\n\r\nTest setup: (chain start is set to 8 validators)\r\n- beacon node 0 <-> 3 validators\r\n- beacon node 1 <-> 3 validators\r\n- beacon node 2 <-> 2 validators\r\n\r\n1.) Upon a new finalized epoch, turn off validators from node 2. \r\nWhat to verify: \r\n* All 3 nodes can advance with the same head root/slot on every slot\r\n* There's a new finalized epoch every epoch\r\n\r\n2.) Upon a new finalized epoch, turn off validators from node 1 and node 2.\r\nWhat to verify: \r\n* All 3 nodes can advance with the same head root/slot on every slot\r\n* There's a no new finalized epoch\r\n\r\n3.) Turn on the validators from node 1.\r\nWhat to verify: \r\n* All 3 nodes can advance with same head root/slot on every slot\r\n* There's a new finalized epoch every epoch before the next 2 epochs\r\n\r\n4.) 50% split network partition, where the connections are broken for `n` epochs and they can be restored. @prestonvanloon mentioned we can use proxy for this",
